fields.title: Grenada
fields.description: Surrounded by the endless blue of the Caribbean, I found myself in a place where water is so scarce. Yet, on Grenada, the struggle for this precious resource is real. As I filmed, I spoke with orange farmers watching their crops wither, their survival dependent on unpredictable rains. Meanwhile, the island is under attack — climate change fuels erosion, with the sea swallowing shores and even cemeteries. The contrast was striking—lush greenery, turquoise waves, and a silent battle for every drop. A journey through an island where water is everywhere, yet never enough

fields.title: California - time of my life
fields.description:
pending four months in San Francisco and California was more than just a professional experience—it was a time of personal growth, discovery, and fulfillment. I lived in the San Francisco Bay Area with other young professionals, surrounded by entrepreneurs, tech innovators, and creative minds. I explored Silicon Valley, Berkeley and Stanford, the startup world, gaining insights that shaped my thinking and career.

But this time was about more than just work. California gave me space to breathe, to reflect, and to reconnect with myself. The open roads took me north to Vancouver, south to Los Angeles, and into the heart of the state’s stunning landscapes. Long drives along the Pacific Coast, the towering redwoods, the energy of new people, and the warmth of the sun all gave me a very deep personal fulfillment—one that still stays with me.

Unfortunately the San Francisco I once knew — the city of my dreams — has changed during the last years, I feel a sens of regret.

fields.title: Sicily, Italy – History, Culture, and Espresso
fields.description: From ancient Greek temples to medieval towns and Baroque cities, Sicily is a place where history comes alive. Traveling its villages and towns, I discovered a mix of cultures that have shaped the island for centuries. Beyond the landmarks, Sicily’s charm is: the scent of fresh espresso, and the warmth of Italian hospitality. Sicily offers a unique blend of past and present.

fields.title: China: High-Tech Cities and Stunning Nature
fields.description:
My trip to China started with a private wedding, took me to political Beijing, the economic powerhouse of Shanghai, and the breathtaking Yellow Mountains. 

But what stayed with me the most were the vast, newly built cities, planned by the government—modern, efficient, yet strangely soulless. Restaurants looked identical, streets were wide but quiet, and many buildings remained empty, waiting for residents who had not yet arrived (instead of photos, I kept the images of these places only in my memory, more vivid than any picture.) At the same time, each of those cities had a huge high-speed train station - so impressive impressively well-organized, and a sign of China’s rapid development.

fields.title: Hawaii – Where Earth Meets the Stars!
fields.description:
Coming from Europe, the sheer distance to Hawaii was astonishing. Flying over endless ocean for hours, I realized just how remote these islands are — isolated in the vast Pacific, far from any continent. The remoteness was striking, but so was the landscape. Lush rainforests, rugged coastlines, and volcanic craters made it clear that nature here follows its own powerful rhythm.

One of the most memorable moments was hiking Mauna Kea, Hawaii’s highest peak at 4,207 meters. The altitude made every step challenging, but reaching the summit, surrounded by telescopes scanning the universe, was a quiet and surreal experience.
